        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 10:14PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1014 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 15 miles west of Ekalaka to 17 miles
northeast of Alzada, or extending from 15 miles west of Ekalaka to
57 miles south of Ekalaka, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ekalaka, Ridgeway, Belltower, Mill Iron, Medicine Rocks State
Park, Capitol and Albion.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
